<recipe>
<title>
Puppy Chow Recipe
</title>
<details>
AUTHOR: I Heart Eating
PREP TIME: 10 minutes
COOK TIME: 2 minutes
TOTAL TIME: 12 minutes
COURSE: Dessert
CUISINE: American
KEYWORD: Chex mix, chocolate, peanut butter
SERVINGS: 12 servings
</details>
<ingredients>
1/4 cup butter
1 1/2 cups chocolate chips&#185;
2/3 cup creamy peanut butter&#178;
1 teaspoon vanilla extract
9 cups Chex rice cereal&#179;
1 1/2 cups powdered sugar
</ingredients>
<instructions>
Place the butter in a large microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave for 40 seconds. The butter should be partially melted.
Add the chocolate chips and peanut butter. Stir in.
Return to microwave, and continue to microwave in 15 second intervals, stirring every 15 seconds, until chocolate is just melted.
Stir to completely combine.
Add vanilla, and stir in.
Add half of the cereal to a large bowl.
Pour half of the chocolate/peanut butter mixture over the cereal, and carefully toss to coat cereal.
Add remaining half cereal to bowl, and pour remaining half chocolate/peanut butter mixture over the top.
Carefully toss to coat the cereal.
Add powdered sugar to a large, resealable plastic bag.
Working in batches, add cereal, seal bag, and then gently shake to coat cereal in powdered sugar.
Let cool to room temperature before storing. 
</instructions>
<cuisine>American</cuisine></recipe>